<refnamediv><refname>imlocalvar</refname><refpurpose>Calculate local image variance.</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>out = imlocalvar(image)
out = imlocalvar(image, window)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>image</term><listitem><para>Input image.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>window</term><listitem><para>Scalar or two-element local window size. Default is <literal>[3 3]</literal>.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>out</term><listitem><para>Local variance image.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection>
<refsection><title>Description</title><para>Returns a local variance map derived from the local standard deviation. High values indicate textured or edge-rich neighborhoods.</para></refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[
image = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/opencv_fruits.jpg"));
image = imresize(rgb2gray(image), [120 160]);
out = imlocalvar(image, [7 7]);
subplot(1, 2, 1);
imshow(image);
subplot(1, 2, 2);
imshow(immat2gray(out), hot(64));
]]></programlisting></refsection>
